rComments: I had her for Calc 1 and got stuck with her for Calc 2 again because of my schedule. Her teaching is very unclear and spends a lot of time on the derivation of things but not on real problems. She falls behind/ gets off schedule often because she's not very organized. She has no grasp of whether students are understanding the material or not.
Calc 2 is the worst class ever, having a bad professor try and teach it to you is even worse.
She mumbles in lectures, and rushes the material a bit. Overall a pretty average lecturer. Not as bad as people assume she is .

Guzman mumbles her lectures and rarely makes eye contact as she speaks. Her lectures are unbearable, and she does a poor job teaching the material. Pray you have a good TA, because the discussion section for this class is important. If you could take this class with another teacher, I highly recommend it.

Don't take her class. She's not going to be helpful at all. One of her famous saying "Well, you should remember from your previous calc class/math 221." And my TA is bad, so I'm planning on learning the materials on my own.

Seriously, during the lectures I have no idea why she is keeping saying things that I've already learnt in MATH 221. Moreover, I found that it hard for me to take notes in her class because she tried to put every single word she said on the board. By the way the board was never clear enough for me to take notes as well. Just one advice, DO NOT take

Really good prof, Dr. Guzman class moves fast, but she puts a bunch of stuff online. Go to lecture because she goes over examples.  Tests not easy but straight forward. Questions are problems from textbook (answers in back), homework and lecture.
Be prepared to teach yourself everything
very hard to follow along with during lecture.

This was without a doubt the worst professor I've ever had. She didn't teach anything on the tests, and really your only hope was attempting to read from the book and going over practice problems on WebAssign and the worksheets/quizzes from discussion. If you get her I wish you luck.

Nice lady, however, as a teacher, she struggled with clarity and explanation. Often times she would place an already solved example on the projector only to take it off ten seconds later saying something akin to, "but you guys already get that, right?". Expect to do a lot on your own or with your TA because practice problems won't happen in lecture

She is a good person! Though she's lecture does not so helpful for understanding calculus and hand-writing notes sometimes are kind of messy, you will find she is willing to help you if go to find her office hour! To my surprise, she remembered every question I asked....
Prepare to work with ur TA

Honestly, one of the worst classes I've ever taken. Her lectures feel long because her explanations are long winded and unclear, and she always uses words like right, so, and anyways. She makes jokes that no one laughs at, tells you to imagine a volume of revolution as a bread chip, and expect to self-study. The only thing that saves you is your TA

Very boring teacher and she is hard to follow. Going to class doesn't help much but I always went because occasionally she'd give out test hints. Tests weren't bad because she reviews material in the lecture before the test.

I went to lecture two times and both times I could not follow Guzman's notes or logic. After three weeks nearly half of the class stopped going to lecture because they were pointless. Just read the text book and ask your T.A. questions and you'll be fine.
boring and not very accommodating hard to understand notes and lectures
Really boring lectures with no help... I learned all things by myself. The only advantage is that you can miss all the lectures.
Calc is tough,  no matter. Okay by me, quite helpful.
Calc is tough no matter what. Okay by me, quite helpful.
